This paper deals with computer vision tasks such as scene segmentation, tracking, and scene understanding, which are typically covered under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper proposes a novel end-to-end differentiable architecture for joint denoising, deblurring, and classification, which involves machine learning techniques and optimization, making it likely to fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of deep neural networks, which is a common technique in the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with image processing, which is a common topic in the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
